<TITLE> Matin calls for broader relief effort </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Jhalakathi, Dec 4 (bdnews24.com)Communications adviser MA Matin Tuesday said the government is pledge-bound to deliver relief and rehabilitate those whose lives have been effaced by Sidr. Matin, who is chief coordinator for relief and rehabilitation activities in the south, made a clarion call to all to participate in the government's efforts to make the relief programme a success. He was speaking to reporters Tuesday morning during distribution of relief materials in Amua Bandarin village, in Khantalia upazila, Jhalakathi, which suffered damaged roads and power outage after Cyclone Sidr struck. The adviser directed the local power authorities to speedily repair the damaged power system, and take assistant from the armed forces in this regard. Matin also directed the Roads and Highways Department to restore land communication by resurfacing damaged roads. He also ordered repair of the Mawa ferry landing station at the earliest. bdnews2
